The paper deals with the design of algorithms for solving linear programs, which is a topic in optimization theory. The use of gradient descent and mirror descent also suggests a connection to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
